   <text>
      <front>
         <pb/>
         <titlePage>
            <docTitle>
               <titlePart>
                  <title>
                     <lb/>
                     <lb/>P O E M S <lb/>
                     <lb/>
                     <hi>on the</hi>
                     <lb/>
                     <lb/>
                     <emph>NAMING OF
                                        PLACES.</emph>
                  </title>
               </titlePart>
            </docTitle>
         </titlePage>
         <pb/>
         <pb/>
         <argument xml:id="ARGUnp">
            <head>
               <hi rend="bold">
                  <lb/>
                  <lb/>
                  <lb/>ADVERTISEMENT. </hi>
            </head>
            <p>By Persons resident in the country and attached to rural
                                   <lb/>objects, many places will be found unnamed or of
                                   un-<lb/>known names, where little Incidents will have occurred,
                                   <lb/>or feelings been experienced, which will have given to such
                                   <lb/>places a private and peculiar interest. From a wish to give
                                   <lb/>some sort of record to such Incidents, or renew the
                                   grati-<lb/>fication of such Feelings, Names have been given to
                                   Places <lb/>by the Author and some of his Friends, and the
                                   follow-<lb/>ing Poems written in consequence. </p>
         </argument>
         <pb/>
      </front>
      <body>
         <p> </p>
      </body>
   </text>
